==English==

===Pronoun phrase===
'''what the fuck?'''

# (''taboo slang'') An intensive form of '''[[what]]''', 

# often used to express nonchalance about the consequences of something one is about to do, "I finally said "What the fuck?" and quit my job."

Abbreviations: [[wtf]], [[WTF]] (emphatic.)


====Translations====
*Italian: [[che cazzo]]?
*Norwegian: [[hva faen]]?
*Russian: [[какого хуя]]?, [[какого черта]]?
*Hebrew: מה לעזאזל?

